  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Cut your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into fries and add them to a large baking tray</p><p>Add a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 25-30 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/thai-style-hake-burger-with-crispy-fries-and-sriracha-mayo/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile pat your <strong>hake fillet[s]</strong> dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Chop the <strong>hake fillet[s]</strong> in half widthways</p><p>Coat the <strong>chopped hake </strong>evenly in your <strong>red Thai curry paste</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/thai-style-hake-burger-with-crispy-fries-and-sriracha-mayo/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span><strong> flour </strong>to a plate with a small pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Press the <strong>chopped hake</strong> into the flour firmly to evenly coat all over</p><p>Meanwhile, peel and dice<strong> half </strong>your <strong>shallot[s]</strong></p><p>Finely slice the <strong>remaining shallot</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/thai-style-hake-burger-with-crispy-fries-and-sriracha-mayo/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>diced shallot</strong> to a bowl with your <strong>rice vinegar </strong>and a small pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>sugar </strong>– this is your <strong>quick-pickled shallot</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>sliced shallot </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until crispy – this is your <strong>crispy shallot</strong></p><p>Once crispy, transfer them to a small bowl or plate<strong> </strong>and reserve the pan</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/thai-style-hake-burger-with-crispy-fries-and-sriracha-mayo/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>coriander </strong>finely, including the stalks</p><p>Top, tail, peel and grate your <strong>carrot[s] </strong>and roughly chop your <strong>roasted peanuts</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>grated carrot</strong>, <strong>chopped coriander </strong>and <strong>chopped roasted peanuts </strong>to the <strong>quick-pickled shallot</strong> and mix to combine – this is your <strong>quick-pickled Asian-style slaw</strong></p><p>Combine your <strong>mayo </strong>and <strong>sriracha </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) in a small bowl<strong> </strong>– this is your <strong>sriracha mayo</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/thai-style-hake-burger-with-crispy-fries-and-sriracha-mayo/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Wipe the reserved pan clean and return it to a high heat</p><p>Slice your <strong>brioche bun[s] </strong>in half (if required!)</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>brioche bun halves</strong>, cut-side down, and cook for 3 min or until coloured and charred on one side only</p><p>Once charred, remove and set aside until serving</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/thai-style-hake-burger-with-crispy-fries-and-sriracha-mayo/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the pan to a high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>coated hake</strong>,<strong> </strong>reduce the heat to medium-high and cook for 4-5 min on each side or until cooked through and lightly crisp – this is your<strong> Thai-style hake</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/thai-style-hake-burger-with-crispy-fries-and-sriracha-mayo/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>To assemble, add a little <strong>sriracha mayo </strong>to the <strong>charred</strong> <strong>brioche bun base </strong>and top with the<strong> Thai-style hake</strong>, <strong>crispy shallot</strong>, some of the <strong>quick-pickled Asian-style slaw </strong>and the <strong>charred brioche bun lid</strong></p><p>Serve with the <strong>crispy fries</strong>, the <strong>remaining quick-pickled Asian-style slaw</strong> and <strong>sriracha mayo</strong> to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
